Questions that arise after the accident: Are stewards in the bus illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long-distance bus is forbidden
In the context of the tragic bus accident of the Student Agency near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel inside the bus.
"If the law is to be strictly and formally respected, the activity of a steward is contrary to the road traffic law," Transport Ministry spokesman Karel Hanzelka said.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck crossing the bus path.
The girl was unfortunately sitting next to the driver in the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she had two other seats at her disposal.
However, the bus can have an accident or even brake abruptly, even when the steward serves coffee or distributes newspapers.
What matters is whether the bus is under its technical data sheet equipped with standing seats or not.
If this equipment for standing seats is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
The long-distance Student Agency coaches do not have standing spaces; this was confirmed in Aktuáln.cz by the director of the company Radim Jan?ura.
“This is an issue that we have dealt with with the ministry and, at first, it prohibits any movement of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got passengers to go to the toilet during the ride as long as they have their own seat,” he said.
The law ignores the steward.
“There is no unambiguous legal interpretation of the role of steward – there are no legal requirements for that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirement prohibits the carrier from offering services.
The road transport law knows only the term vehicle receiver; it does not define his rights and duties,” Hanzelka added more ambiguously.
Josef Pokorn, head of the road vehicle traffic department, said the law dealt with the issue adequately.
“It all depends on whether the coach has permission to offer standing seats in its approval.
It’s all in there,” he said.
Buses are divided into urban, where there are standing places and limited maximum speed, long-distance with standing places and higher authorized speed, and long-distance buses without standing places with the highest authorized maximum speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
Like on a plane, says an expert.
Jaroslav Ho?n, an expert at BESIP (Road Traffic Safety) on transport safety, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"In regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of service in airplanes.
Nor is he sure when a turbulence will occur and the air hostess can hit her head."
“But if the bus braked abruptly, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
Same way as on an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of the stewards through internal prescriptions," he says and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the issue is not resolved.
Janura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer stewards services.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the manager does not consider their job as a risky job.
"However, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky profession, I will remove it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper at boarding.
It would also reduce costs,” he says.
The safety concern is the reason given by the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexeï Litvine, who ensures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We've opposed them from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a deadly accident," he told T?den.cz a year ago.
A huge tragedy has arrived.
A young hostess from the Plzec region, who had worked for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop strip without using a flasher and blocked the way to the bus.
The driver of the latter trying to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he bordered it on his right side.
Janura refuses that the two seats reserved for the stewards’ rest have been sold.
"In the case of long-distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these seats, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the family of the girl, the agency will not wait for the judgement of the court, but as for the financial compensation, she also counts on the culprit.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the movements of stewards on board the bus.
"But it has not reached any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the points system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the mobile phone behind the wheel," says expert Ho?n.
“The Ministry of Transport does not consider stewards’ activity to be something that would fundamentally jeopardize the safety of passengers,” Hanzelka said, adding that control of the safety of buses is under the power of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
The hopes of the Düsseldorfers rest on Frankfurt.
The big words were not lacking in the letter addressed by the WestLB board of directors to the employees of the house.
Through a union of the entities of the Düsseldorf financial institution with the Frankfurt Deka-Bank, "the central financial market institution of the financial group of the Sparkasse" could be formed, according to the letter made public on Monday.
The WestLB would bring a "competence block" coupled with sustainable productivity in such a case.
All in all, such a relationship could be the decisive starting point for other concentrations in the Länder' banking sector.
This is what it looks like when a board wants to demonstrate its ability to act in difficult times.
Because the WestLB, injured, is always under great pressure.
It was not only the European Commission but also the Federal Financial Services Supervisory Authority that made it clear to the government of the Land of North Rhine-Westphalia that time was in the search for a future solution.
However, there has been talk for some time now - also on the Frankfurt side - of a relationship of some form between Deka bank, which knows the customers of the Sparkasse through their investment funds, and the WestLB.
It is true that Deta-Bank chief Franz Waas made it clear at the presentation of the half-year figures at the end of August that he saw no meaning in the merger of the Mainzer Landstrasse house with a Land bank, be it Helaba or WestLB.
However, the Deka Board of Directors, each of which is supported by the Länder banks and savings bank groups, has instructed the Steering Committee to conduct talks with the WestLB for joint commercial activities.
It could then be the debit of the financial market, or parts of it.
However, the talks have only just begun, it is said in the financial centre.
This is not the first time that the Deta-Bank, with its 3,000 employees, counts for one of the largest employers in the Frankfurt financial centre, has come into play when it comes to the consolidation of the savings sector.
In 2003 it was believed for a while that the Deta-Bank could merge with the Land Bank of Rhineland-Palatinate and Halbab.
Nothing came out of this ternary bouquet.
As soon as the plans had been made public, the Hessian government was against any participation of Hellaba in them.
Later, the other two houses did not join.
The Land Bank of Rhineland-Palatinate was instead attached to the Land Bank of Baden-Wuttenberg in Stuttgart.
But there have always been new negotiations on the merger of the Deka-Bank with Länder banks.
Lastly, however, Hellaba chairman Günther Merl had spoken out against any commercial merger strategy with his bank.
Regardless of this, the feeling seems to be spreading that the regrouping of the various institutions of the public sector is particularly urgent.
Now that the Bavarian Land Parliament election has passed, a union of the BayernLB with the Baden-Wuttenberg Land Bank could become a reality first.
