If the pressure for new mergers were to increase, the potential partners would gradually escape.
In the South, it would now be a junior partner, although it has so far withstood the crisis better than the banks in Munich and Stuttgart.
The Hesse-Thuringe savings and transfer group, which owns 85 percent of Helaba’s capital, pulled a lock earlier this year on the entire union with WestLB.
The NordLB would be left to the rigor.
