The New York Stock Exchange experienced a historic drop Monday after the House rejected the Paulson bank bailout: the Dow Jones lost 6.98%, an unprecedented loss approaching 800 points, and the Nasdaq 9.14%.
The Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) plunged 777.68 points to 1O.365.45 points.
