The value of the Prague Stock Exchange is estimated to be between 5 and 10 billion Czech kroner by market specialists.
Based on an agreement between the shareholders, about 90% of the papers would be sold.
The largest owner of the Prague stock exchange is investment bank Patria Finance, with about 25 percent stakes, followed by the 14.7 percent of the bank Ceská Sporitelna and the Tiger Holding Four S.a.r.l. with 13.5 percent.
